message.text:
Today is バレンタインデー or VALENTINE'S DAY! 
In Japan, it is common for girls to give out chocolates to boys as a gift to show her love. 

However, a recent trend is to give chocolates to your friends, not to your crush. It's called 友チョコ TOMO-CHOKO, or FRIEND-CHOCOLATE. 

What's more, boys are encouraged to gift chocolate to girls these days. This phenomenon is calld 逆チョコ GYAKU-CHOKO, or REVERSED-CHOCOLATE. 
Hmm...to whom and what chocolate will you send today? 

http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1901&p=1&q=バレンタイン&source=search&lang=en
